
1. description

a server that binds itself to a TCP port, listens for incoming squidguard statements and sends the request to one of num_daemons squidguards


          --------------------      ---- squidguard
  IO     |                    |    |
---------+  url_check server  +----+---- squidguard
  TCP    |                    |    |
          --------------------       ...
                                   |
                                    ---- squidguard

2. dependencies

 - epoll aware OS (Linux >=2.6, FreeBSD)
 - >=net-proxy/squidguard-1.5_beta-r1
 - net-analyzer/netcat6 (from http://netcat6.sourceforge.net/) for testing. net-analyzer/netcat from http://nc110.sourceforge.net/ will NOT work.


3. how to compile/test

 $ make && ./url_checkd --num-daemons 8

  # in a different terminal
 $ bash test_adblock.sh a
 $ bash test_adblock.sh b



